'''Dana Jurásková''' (born 21 September 1961) is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[politician]]. She was the Minister of Health in the [[caretaker government]] of [[Jan Fischer (politician)|Jan Fischer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.praguepost.com/news/1267-interim-government-takes-charge.html |title=Interim government takes charge |publisher=The Prague Post |date=2009-05-14 |accessdate=2009-05-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606100712/http://www.praguepost.com/news/1267-interim-government-takes-charge.html |archivedate=2011-06-06 |df= }}</ref>

