{{Infobox person | name=Haruchika Noguchi | image=Haruchika-noguchi-portrait.jpg | imagesize=120x160 | birth_date=September 1911 | birth_place=[[Ueno, Tokyo]], [[Japan]] | death_date=1976 | death_place= [[Japan]] | nationality={{flagicon|JPN}} [[Japanese people|Japanese]] | occupation=[[Seitai]] founder |}} {{Nihongo|'''Haruchika Noguchi'''|野口 晴哉|Noguchi Haruchika|September 1911 – 1976}} was the Japanese founder of ''[[Seitai]]''.<ref name="OSB">[http://www.zensei.co.jp/englishbookpage/englishpage2.htm Order, Spontaneity and the Body] by Haruchika Noguchi. Tokyo, Japan, [[Zensei]], 1985, paperback. {{ISBN|4-915417-00-X}}..</ref> He established the concept of ''[[taiheki]]''.
